A "fault proof program" emulates validating a rollup onchain.

Normally, a server reads data from a node (op-node) over RPC, then processes it (op-geth), storing it in a DB.

Fault proofs programs emulate RPCs onchain by providing witness data.

Instead of "reading", you're "proving" at every step, all in EVM memory!
